Undef MAX before redefining in vnetInt.h

Kernel 6.11+ defines a generic MAX() macro in <linux/minmax.h> that
conflicts with vmnet local MAX() in vnetInt.h, producing redefinition
warnings on every compile of bridge.c, driver.c, etc.

Cosmetic on most kernels but becomes a hard failure with -Werror.

--- a/vmnet-only/vnetInt.h
+++ b/vmnet-only/vnetInt.h
@@ -47,6 +47,7 @@
 #define LOG(level, args)
 #endif
 
+#undef MAX
 #define MAX(_a, _b)   (((_a) > (_b)) ? (_a) : (_b))
 
 /*
